description.narrative: In 2019, the National Newborn Campaign was scaled-up, reaching 10 million people through mass media, and 600,000 households through community mobilisation by 3,000 trained frontline workers. A total of 240,000 pre-primary age children across eight districts were informed and engaged on healthy behaviours through a mosque-based entertainment-education package supported by 2,000 trained imams and 1,800 trained female teachers. Approximately 300,000 Rohingya households were routinely engaged on life-saving practices in Cox's Bazar, supported by intensified radio programming and campaign outreach during the year. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
